Follow @wendelishh for more easy air fryer recipes. Save this video for the perfect side dish or snack.

Plantains are very versatile and are a rich source of fiber. It can be prepared in many ways - steamed, boiled, grilled or baked. I’ve recently used the air fryer for a healthier version compared to the traditional fried plantains. Full recipe below xx

Healthy Air Fryer Plantains

Ingredients
2 plantains, ripe
3 teaspoon cooking oil
Salt for taste  
Wash, peel and cut plantains to your desire. Spray oil or lightly coat plantains with oil. Turn on air fryer to 400°. Cook plantain for 10-12 minutes, flipping over half way through. Enjoy!

TIP: You can also make them sweeter to serve as a dessert by sprinkling cinnamon and sugar on the top. Full recipe below

MANGO TALKARIE 🥭🇹🇹 follow @wendelishh for easy Caribbean recipes and save this video for your next side dish.

Mango Talkarie is usually made during Diwali season but Mama Delishh makes this dish all year round. It can be eaten on its own or it makes for the perfect side dish when serving any curry dishes. The best season is mango season 😉. Full recipe below. Enjoy xx

Mango Talkarie 

Ingredients
5 large green mangos 
2 cups brown sugar
1 large onion, diced
3 scotch bonnet pepper 
5 garlic, crushed
1 cup water
4 tbsp amchar masala
1 tsp cumin seed
3 tbsp cooking oil 
Salt for taste

✨GLAZED BAKED HAM✨ follow @wendelishh for more Holiday recipes. Save this video for the juiciest centrepiece for your holiday table.

Ingredients 

1 Large (4-5 pounds) Shoulder Bone-in Ham 
6  round Selection Pineapple slices
20-25 Irresistible Spice Cloves
6 Maraschino Cherries

For The Glaze
1 cup Light brown sugar
1/4 cup Section Mandarin juice 
1/4 Orange juice
3 tablespoons Orange zest
1/2 cup Honey
1/4 cup Irresponsibles Thyme 

Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Place ham in a roasting pan. Cover with foil and bake for one hour. Remove ham from the oven every 20 mins and brush with glaze. After one hour turn oven to 400 degrees F, remove foil and bake for an additional 20 to 30 minutes, brushing ham with glaze every 10 minutes. Let ham rest for 15 minutes to lock in the juices, slice and serve.

TIP: Use the ham bone and any trimmings to make a delicious soup afterward.

Trini Salt-fish Accra 🇹🇹

The number on the scale, the tag on your clothes, they don’t mean anything in the bigger picture of LIFE. The other day I wore a size 10 jeans and this dress is a size 7. Don’t let the number trip you out, beauty isn’t one size fits all, you’re gorgeous the way you are; today 🩵

You’re going to come in contact with an awful lot of people who are at their absolute breaking point this holiday season. Friends, family, co-workers, teachers, strangers in the grocery store and retailer workers. 

While this may be the merriest time of the year for some, it’s the saddest, loneliest, most stressful and heartbreaking for so many others. 

We’re all busy, but we’re not too busy to be kind, caring and patient. Remember the best thing you can give someone right now is love 💫♥️✨

#bekind #selflove #seasonofgiving

🎄Tis the season of giving and my friends at McDonald’s Canada kicked off the Season of Giving. The Season of Giving is a series of moments for McDonald’s to thank you to the people and organizations making a difference in our communities.

I had the privilege of visiting the RMHC Toronto where families stay together while their child is being treated at a nearby hospital. It’s a warm and compassionate home where they can sleep, share meals, do laundry, attend accredited education programs at school and be supported by other families. 

Supporting RMHC is super easy too - you can Round Up for RMHC to the nearest dollar with the difference donated to RMHC across Canada at McDonald’s all year long!
